{{mergeinto|Slavic calendar|date=October 2017}} The [[Macedonian language]] has two sets of names of the months of the [[Gregorian calendar]]. The most commonly used set of names is derived from the [[Latin]] month names and these are used by the vast majority of the [[Macedonians (ethnic group)|Macedonian population]]. However, there is also a set of older names for the twelve months of [[Slavic languages|Slavic origin]] that differ from the Latin month names, although their usage is [[Archaism|archaized]] and largely restricted to folk literature and religious calendars issued by the [[Macedonian Orthodox Church]].
The origin of the Macedonian month names is closely related to the [[Agriculture|agricultural]] activities that occur in the corresponding period, or to the [[weather]] condition common for that period. Some months have alternative names in different regions. The usage of modern Latin month names among Macedonians started towards the end of the [[19th century]], as a result of mass education.
